<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Scaled_correlation_coeffici=
ent">Scaled correlation coefficient</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/w/index.php?title=3DPearson_correlation_coefficient&amp;action=3Dedit&a=
mp;section=3D28" title=3D"Edit section: Scaled correlation coefficient"><sp=
an>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></d=
iv>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scaled_correlation" =
title=3D"Scaled correlation">Scaled correlation</a></div>
<p>Scaled correlation is a variant of Pearson's correlation in which the ra=
nge of the data is restricted intentionally and in a controlled manner to r=
eveal correlations between fast components in <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Time_series" title=3D"Time series">time series</a>.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-Nikolicetal_45-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Pearson_correlation_coefficient#cite_note-Nikolicetal-45"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>43<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup> Scaled correlation is defined as average correlation across short se=
gments of data.
</p><p>Let <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span c=
lass=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none=
;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displays=
tyle K}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>K</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle K}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/2b76fce82a62ed5461908f0dc8f037de4e3686b0" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:2.066ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle K}"=
></span> be the number of segments that can fit into the total length of th=
e signal <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span cla=
ss=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"=
><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaysty=
le T}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>T</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle T}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/ec7200acd984a1d3a3d7dc455e262fbe54f7f6e0" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.636ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle T}"=
></span> for a given scale <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element=
-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=
=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" altt=
ext=3D"{\displaystyle s}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>s</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle s}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/01d131dfd7673938b947072a13a9744fe997e632" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.09ex; height:1.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle s}">=
</span>:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e K=3D\operatorname {round} \left({\frac {T}{s}}\right).}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>K</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>round</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mfrac>
              <mi>T</mi>
              <mi>s</mi>
            </mfrac>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle K=3D\operator=
name {round} \left({\frac {T}{s}}\right).}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/7a18a5b1b26d158dc37bd2b34fe0921ee1c73dc5" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.505ex; width:17.656ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle K=
=3D\operatorname {round} \left({\frac {T}{s}}\right).}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>The scaled correlation across the entire signals <span class=3D"mwe-math=
-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe=
-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.or=
g/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle {\bar {r}}_{s}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mover>
                <mi>r</mi>
                <mo stretchy=3D"false">=C2=AF<!-- =C2=AF --></mo>
              </mover>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>s</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\bar {r}}_{s=
}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f1fb173b0ab9244d34f1fc5ceb57f7cb091bc5fb" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:2.295ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\b=
ar {r}}_{s}}"></span> is then computed as
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\bar {r}}_{s}=3D{\frac {1}{K}}\sum \limits _{k=3D1}^{K}r_{k},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mover>
                <mi>r</mi>
                <mo stretchy=3D"false">=C2=AF<!-- =C2=AF --></mo>
              </mover>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>s</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mi>K</mi>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <munderover>
          <mo movablelimits=3D"false">=E2=88=91<!-- =E2=88=91 --></mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>K</mi>
          </mrow>
        </munderover>
        <msub>
          <mi>r</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\bar {r}}_{s=
}=3D{\frac {1}{K}}\sum \limits _{k=3D1}^{K}r_{k},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/d3c9d6d707342d0e2f0ce3b221d114124ac6ef20" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -3.005ex; width:15.209ex; height:7.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
bar {r}}_{s}=3D{\frac {1}{K}}\sum \limits _{k=3D1}^{K}r_{k},}"></span></dd>=
</dl>
<p>where <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span cla=
ss=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"=
><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaysty=
le r_{k}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>r</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle r_{k}}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/9b28e0e640d099f3676330bd4f604ae15c37bb4f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:2.137ex; height:2.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle r_{=
k}}"></span> is Pearson's coefficient of correlation for segment <span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-math=
ml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"htt=
p://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle k}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>k</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle k}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/c3c9a2c7b599b37105512c5d570edc034056dd40" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.211ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle k}"=
></span>.
</p><p>By choosing the parameter <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-e=
lement-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" =
style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"=
 alttext=3D"{\displaystyle s}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>s</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle s}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/01d131dfd7673938b947072a13a9744fe997e632" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.09ex; height:1.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle s}">=
</span>, the range of values is reduced and the correlations on long time s=
cale are filtered out, only the correlations on short time scales being rev=
ealed. Thus, the contributions of slow components are removed and those of =
fast components are retained.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Pearson's_distance"><span i=
d=3D"Pearson.27s_distance"></span>Pearson's distance</h3><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DPearson_correlation_coefficient&am=
p;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D29" title=3D"Edit section: Pearson's distance=
"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></spa=
n></div>
<p>A distance metric for two variables <i>X</i> and <i>Y</i> known as <i>Pe=
arson's distance</i> can be defined from their correlation coefficient as<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-46" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Pearson_correlation_coefficient#cite_note-46"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>44<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e d_{X,Y}=3D1-\rho _{X,Y}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>d</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>X</mi>
            <mo>,</mo>
            <mi>Y</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>=CF=81<!-- =CF=81 --></mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>X</mi>
            <mo>,</mo>
            <mi>Y</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle d_{X,Y}=3D1-\=
rho _{X,Y}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/e68aeaeed324bc9a50c6e3215f77ef7986038a89" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
